# Cursor AI Configuration for FlowFox Creatives Project

## Rules and Configuration

### TypeScript
- Use strict mode TypeScript
- Avoid `any` types, always define types explicitly
- Use Zod for runtime validation of API endpoints

### Next.js 15 App Router
- Use Server Components by default
- Mark Client Components with 'use client' directive
- Use async/await for Server Components

### Code Style
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Follow naming conventions (camelCase for variables, PascalCase for components)
- Add loading states for all async operations
- Proper error handling with try/catch blocks

### API Responses
- Structure: `{ success: boolean, data?, error? }`
- Use NextResponse for API routes
- Proper HTTP status codes (400, 404, 500)

### Database
- Use Prisma for all database operations
- Use transactions for complex operations
- Proper error handling for database errors

### UI/UX
- Loading states for all async operations
- Disabled buttons during processing
- Clear error messages for users
- Responsive design (mobile-first)

### Comments
- Comments in English for business logic
- JSDoc for complex functions
